&#9997;Under construction..............

Osmosis is a chemical process in which the solvent molecules move from a region of higher solvent concentration through a semipermeable membrane to a region of lower solvent concentration. The membrane must be permeable to the solvent molecules, but not to the solute molecules.

Osmosis plays a critically important role in biology. Without osmosis, water would not have been able to reach cells and there would not have been life in our current form. &quot;No physical phenomenon has any greater importance in biology than does osmosis.&quot; Thus did the Editor of The American Journal of Physiology introduce the 1979 Forum on Osmosis.

